frus:attachment.p:
The President of the United States of America, and His Majesty the Emperor of Austria, King of Bohemia, &c., and Apostolic King of Hungary, mutually desirous
of extending to the officers and crews of the vessels of either country who may be involved in judicial proceedings in the courts of the other, ail proper facilities for the defense of their personal rights, have resolved to that end to conclude an article supplemental to the consular convention of July 11, 1870, between the two countries, and have appointed as their plenipotentiaries, to wit:
The President of the United States, Frederick T. Frelinghuysen, Secretary of State;
And His Imperial and Royal Apostolic Majesty,—— ——;
